{meta: title Forever Was The Name Of Our Sunshine}
{meta: artist Faron Young}
{meta: writer Dallas Frazier and Arthur Leo Owens}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Happy was the feelin' that you [D7]gave me when we met
[C]Tender was the touch that caused my [D7]heart to fall in [G]debt
Gentle was the hand that reached and [D7]placed a ring on mine
And for[C]ever was the [D7]name of our [G]sunshine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Breakin' was the sound that stopped the [D7]singin' in my heart
Hurtin' was the emptiness that [C]taught me how to [G]cry
Sadness was the unexpected [C]wind that blew so hard
Leavin' nothin' but a memory of the [D7]time
When for[C]ever was the [D7]name of our [G]sunshine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
